&lt;p&gt;Tecovas was founded with the simple goal of making the world&#39;s best western boots, apparel and leather goods - and selling them at a fair price. We are a brand revolutionizing a category and welcoming first-time boot buyers and western enthusiasts alike.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tecovas&lt;/strong&gt; is looking for an Apparel Product Developer to manage all new Seasonal Apparel Development from Brief Handoff to Line Close. Reporting directly to the Apparel Product Developer Manager, you will oversee the entire apparel development process, ensuring designs are executed to meet quality, cost, and timeline goals while collaborating with cross-functional teams and managing factory relationships.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is required to be based in Austin, TX. Candidates must either be currently located in or willing to relocate to Austin, TX.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work within our apparel milestone process to deliver all protos through the various stages, starting at design handoff and ending at production and participating in QC for ongoing issues.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with our Tecovas merchants and designers to assure the product is being developed and delivered correctly on time and at margin target.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the technical design teams to ensure all protos are fit-approved by Line Freeze.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate with sourcing team members to assure all materials meet the Tecovas “Functional” guidelines.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create timely and accurate seasonal tech packs in the PLM system.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support managing the weekly tracker, communicating the status of development &amp;amp; protos cross category: Merchandising, Design, and Supply Chain.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Design to understand seasonal trends and fabrication needs. Identify and source fabrics that align with the creative brief while meeting price point and margin targets.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a hands-on partner for hybrid team members.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have a growth and problem solving mindset around process and workflow with cross functional teams.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Visit factories to manage the development of the products through various phases.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience we’re looking for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of Deep knowledge of garment assembly, including but not limited to: Cut &amp;amp; Sew Knits, Wovens, Tailoring, Denim/Wash processing, and technical outerwear construction.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of experience fitting and approving products at Line Freeze.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience in Apparel Costing (CMT), fabric consumption/yield analysis, and overseeing Fabric Testing.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in Garment Construction, Fit, Calendar Management, Materials, and Tech Pack creation.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in a PLM system is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you bring to the table:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have the ability to adapt in real time.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You possess a positive, team-based attitude.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are a self starter and are able to think and work like an entrepreneur.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have excellent written and verbal communication skills.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full Time Benefits &amp;amp; Perks:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We offer insurance plans that pay 79-90% of your health premium coverage and 100% of your dental &amp;amp; vision insurance coverage for your family/dependents&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;401(k) match&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid Parental Leave&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexib

&lt;p&gt;Tecovas was founded with the simple goal of making the world&#39;s best western boots, apparel and leather goods - and selling them at a fair price. We are a brand revolutionizing a category and welcoming first-time boot buyers and western enthusiasts alike.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tecovas&lt;/strong&gt; is looking for an Assistant Designer to support the Women’s Footwear Design team in creating innovative, brand-right footwear. Reporting directly to the Design Director, you will collaborate closely with cross-functional partners to turn seasonal direction, market insights, and trend research into commercial product concepts that reflect the Tecovas brand.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is required to be based in Austin, TX. Candidates must either be currently located in or willing to relocate to Austin, TX.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the design team in translating seasonal direction and market research into new and relevant concepts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in developing upper designs, outsoles, trims, and embellishments that align with Tecovas’ brand DNA.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create detailed sketches, CADs, and tech packs using Adobe Illustrator, Photoshop, and PLM systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional teams to ensure all design details are clearly communicated.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support design team in preparation of all design and prototype reviews; making sure to take accurate notes and help with design updates and sample corrections.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Product Development to ensure all footwear samples are accurate upon arrival and help make any necessary callouts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in fittings to ensure integrity of designs while delivering out-of-the box comfort.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and contribute to a digital asset library with swatches, components, templates, and more.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organize inspiration, samples, and prototypes to support the design process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel internationally and attend tradeshows and events as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience we’re looking for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Footwear Design, Industrial Design, or equivalent design experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1+ years of relevant experience in women’s footwear design or designer capacity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in creating CADs, technical drawings, and tech packs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with PLM systems a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bonus points for experience in leather goods and an understanding of Western lifestyle or culture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you bring to the table:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are passionate about product design and craftsmanship - especially leather and footwear.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are detail oriented, organized, and resourceful.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You can manage multiple priorities and deliver high-quality work on time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have excellent communication skills and the ability to clearly present your ideas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full Time Benefits &amp;amp; Perks:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We offer insurance plans that pay 79-90% of your health premium coverage and 100% of your dental &amp;amp; vision insurance coverage for your family/dependents&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;401(k) match&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid Parental Leave&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible PTO policy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Corporate wellness program&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive salary - &lt;em&gt;$65,000-70,000/annum (commensurate with experience)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Eligibility to participate in Corporate Bonus Program&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous employee discounts!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tecovas&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;is passionate about offering an incredible customer experience for first-time boot buyers and western enthusiasts alike! We’re looking for a talented&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Full-Time&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Assistant Store Manager&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;that will contribute to a profitable and customer-centric environment through the development of a team and management of our total store operations. They will support product flow and apply merchant and customer service skills to curate a compelling in-store experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Responsibilities will include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CUSTOMER EXPERIENCE&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cultivates an environment of genuine customer connection&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrates extraordinary service and acts as a brand ambassador reflective of the company values&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitates an energized pace, positive service environment and team development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Delivers high-quality product services with attention to detail - such as branding, debossing, boot stretching, brim shaping, and boot shines - to ensure a premium customer experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understands an OMNI Channel business - implements processes and utilizes tools to better service the customer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;LEADERSHIP &amp;amp; TEAM MANAGEMENT&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supports the Store Manager in recruiting, hiring, and retaining top talent&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supports the Store Manager in creating and maintaining a succession strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foster a culture of strong communication and teamwork in order to ensure a seamless balance between operational, visual and customer priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provides real-time feedback, coaching and training to team members, escalating issues as needed to Store Manager&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;TRAINING &amp;amp; DEVELOPMENT&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver world-class, in-person training (in conjunction with e-learning) to all new team members&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure timely completion of new hire training paths&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Meet regularly with the Tecovas HQ Retail Training team or field leaders to check in on team progress&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Suggest improvements or new programs related to retail training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the compliance of all training activities with established policies and best practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with store leadership to prepare, plan, schedule, and execute new hire training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with store leadership and HQ partners to facilitate and organize ongoing training in store locations, including training for new products and services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend regular training meetings to ensure understanding of necessary information&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;VISUAL MERCHANDISING&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Productive planning, presetting, and on-time execution of visual directives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Submit store photos as requested and complete feedback given by HQ&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in visual training calls with HQ partners to support new product launches&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with store leadership team to ensure VM standards are upheld, and replenishment tasks are completed&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support store presentation through sell through and markdown cycles&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain in-store marketing elements and accurate presentation of store collateral&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with store manager to ensure schedule is reflective of visual set times for product launches&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with store leaders for new hire visual training&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversight of sales floor and windows to ensure proper lighting placement, store cleanliness, maintenance of window displays

